Gini Coefficient

In economics, the Gini coefficient is a measure of statistical dispersion intended to represent the income or wealth distribution of a nation’s residents.
In this case the Gini coefficient measures the price distribution in managers’ draft auction purchases. A low score would indicate a more even distribution (meaning more equally priced players) and a high score an uneven distribution (a few high priced and a lot of low priced players).
